  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed banner advertisement attached to the scaffolding posts at the front elevation of Cornwell House, by reason of its size, siting and prominence, would be an intrusive and discordant feature that would be harmful to the setting of the surrounding listed buildings, including the Grade II Cornwell House and the Grade II* Sessions House. The advertisement would fail to preserve or enhance the character or appearance of the Clerkenwell Green Conservation Area. The proposed adverts are contrary to policy DM2.1, DM2.3 and DM 2.6 of the Development Management Policies 2013, the Islington Urban Design Guide 2017, Conservation Area Design Guidelines & the NPPF 2018."
